{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idbda373d2-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6374d"},"text":"§ 6374d.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Studies and reports","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbda373d3-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374d/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Methanol study","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbda373d4-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374d/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The Secretary shall study methanol plants, including the costs and practicability of such plants, that are—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbda373d5-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374d/a/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" capable of utilizing current domestic supplies of unutilized natural gas;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbda373d6-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374d/a/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" relocatable; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbda373d7-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374d/a/1/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" suitable for natural gas to methanol conversion by natural gas distribution companies.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbda373d8-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374d/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" For purposes of this subsection, the term “unutilized natural gas” means gas that is available in small remote fields and cannot be economically transported to natural gas pipelines, or gas the quality of which is so poor that extensive and uneconomic pretreatment is required prior to its introduction into the natural gas distribution system.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbda373d9-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374d/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Secretary shall submit a report under this subsection to the Committees on Commerce, Science, and Transportation and Governmental Affairs of the Senate, and the Committee on Energy and Commerce of the House of Representatives, no later than ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-09-30"},"text":"September 30, 1990","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbda373da-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374d/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Omitted","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbda373db-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374d/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Public participation","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Adequate opportunity shall be provided for public comment on the reports required by this section before they are submitted to the Congress, and a summary of such comments shall be attached to such reports.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idbda373dc-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/163/tIII/s400EE"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–163, title III, § 400EE","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/494/s4/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–494, § 4(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-10-14"},"text":"Oct. 14, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/2447"},"text":"102 Stat. 2447","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idbda373dd-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idbda373de-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idbda373df-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This part, referred to in subsec. (b)(1)(A), was in the original “the Alternative Motor Fuels Act of 1988”, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/494"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–494","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-10-14"},"text":"Oct. 14, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/2441"},"text":"102 Stat. 2441","children":[],"tail":", which is classified principally to this part. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title of 1988 Amendment note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s6201"},"text":"section 6201 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idbda373e0-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b) of this section, which required the Administrator of the Environmental Protection Agency to submit biennially to Congress a report which includes a comprehensive analysis of the environmental impacts associated with the production and use of alternative motor vehicle fuels under this part and an extended forecast of the environmental effects of such production and use, terminated, effective ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-05-15"},"text":"May 15, 2000","children":[],"tail":", pursuant to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/66/s3003"},"text":"section 3003 of Pub. L. 104–66","children":[],"tail":", as amended, set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t31/s1113"},"text":"section 1113 of Title 31","children":[],"tail":", Money and Finance. See, also, the 25th item on page 163 of House Document No. 103–7."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idbda373e1-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"changeOfName","id":"idbda373e2-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Change of Name","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Committee on Governmental Affairs of Senate changed to Committee on Homeland Security and Governmental Affairs of Senate, effective ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2005-01-04"},"text":"Jan. 4, 2005","children":[],"tail":", by Senate Resolution No. 445, One Hundred Eighth Congress, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-10-09"},"text":"Oct. 9, 2004","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Committee on Energy and Commerce of House of Representatives treated as referring to Committee on Commerce of House of Representatives by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/14/s1/a"},"text":"section 1(a) of Pub. L. 104–14","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t2/s21"},"text":"section 21 of Title 2","children":[],"tail":", The Congress. Committee on Commerce of House of Representatives changed to Committee on Energy and Commerce of House of Representatives, and jurisdiction over matters relating to securities and exchanges and insurance generally transferred to Committee on Financial Services of House of Representatives by House Resolution No. 5, One Hundred Seventh Congress, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2001-01-03"},"text":"Jan. 3, 2001","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
